# EXAMPLE / format reference for the fleet registry.
# The LIVE registry is host state and lives at ~/.aqua-matrix-test/consultants.registry
# (it lists THIS host's actual consultants). roll-consultant-fleet.sh reads that path by
# default (override with CONSULTANTS_REGISTRY=...).
#
# Format: one TAB-separated row per dedicated single-target consultant:
#     label <TAB> target-MXID <TAB> display(doc-only)
# - label   : lowercase [a-z0-9-]; selects the container/config/persist/watcher names.
#             Rows whose first column isn't a valid slug are skipped with a warning.
#             `generic` is RESERVED: it selects the UN-LABELED operator-bound consultant
#             (aqua-agent-aqua-consultant-1) and rolls via --generic instead of --label.
# - target  : the peer MXID this consultant answers (doc-only here; the roll uses
#             --keep-config and reads the authoritative target from the on-disk config).
# - display : human label, documentation only.
# Lines that are blank or whose first non-whitespace char is '#' are ignored.
#
# DO NOT list this Tim-bound container here (different backend, rolled separately):
#   - aqua-agent-tim-channel          (SEED=0 bash ~/recreate-tim-channel.sh)
#
# Snapshot of the live fleet at 2026-06-08 (illustrative):
carlottas	@did-pkh-eip155-1-0x...:matrix.inblock.io	Carlotta's Aqua Consultant
garys	@quartermonk:matrix.jembawan.com	Gary's Aqua Consultant
zdnaef	@did-key-zDnaef...:matrix.inblock.io	Aqua Consultant (zDnaef…)
zdnaez	@did-key-zdnaezp...:matrix.inblock.io	Aqua Consultant (Aubert)
gawain	@did-key-zdnaenq...:matrix.inblock.io	Aqua Consultant (Gawain)
generic	@did-pkh-eip155-1-0x...:matrix.inblock.io	Aqua Consultant (operator's own, un-labeled)
